content.description: This is all bolts but of an old school style. Enjoy!
content.location: There's a shorter rock to the right of the main (left) face with one route Talon.

content.description:
A one pitch climb done as two due to rope drag.

P1 starts on a wide lieback then traverses left on flake underclings to a notch in a small roof (crux), one bolt above the crux, then a ledge with chains.

P2 Go left to a 5.7 chimney or right on more flakes (5.9) to a bolt, then some zig-zagging to a final bolt and cool exposed traverse to the arete.

Rap off same anchor as for Brentwood Buttress.

Cool moves on this thing but some flaky rock.
content.protection: Standard rack, P1 has one bolt P2 to the right has  2 bolts, a piton, and then a third bolt.
content.location: Starts in the middle of the left face on wide layback.
